    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "That's a great start. I want to make sure the post doesn't sound too one-sided or academically dry, though. Could you help me frame these arguments in a way that addresses the common \"checks and balances\" or \"safety\" arguments people use to justify regulation? I want to show that those \"safety\" concerns are actually just thinly veiled attempts at censorship.",
